      <h1>Career Remedies For You</h1>
                 
                  <p >
                  <p>Different people have varied personalities and preferences depending on their Zodiac sign. If you are taking up a job which suits your personality, positively shapes your energy level and exploits your true potential, then you will be chuffed at the end of the day. <strong>Expert astrologers at Astroyogi,</strong> guide you on the best-suited career choices according to your zodiac sign and some career remedies if you are not satisfied with your work.</p>

<p><strong>Aries (21 March-20 April</strong>)</p>

<p>Aries natives are independent, enthusiastic and strong-willed. Aries will often have a manic nature. They are usually seen as having a restless and upfront personality. They are not supposed to be bounded to a desk job which will not feed their curiosity. If you are an Aries and not satisfied with the current job or if you are facing difficulties with improving your career, <strong>our experts</strong> advise you to perform a Surya Namaskar puja in the morning and offer water to Sun God in a copper vessel.</p>

<p>Due to their bravery (and their impulsivity) they are heroes of our lives- the police officers and firefighters. They are excellent promoters and may find the world of advertising and public relations appealing to their outgoing nature.</p>

<p><strong>Taurus (21 April-20 May)</strong></p>

<p>Taureans are extremely dependable and hard-working people. They are neat in their jobs, grounded, practical and make a great team player. Being good with their figures and calculations, they can do well in banks and in the scientific stream. They would do well in the research department too.</p>

<p>Being a Taurean you like stability in your life and anything that disturbs your stability can, in turn, affects your career.Keeping crystal Sri yantra of about 350 gms can help in shaping your energy towards a better stable career. This improves Lakshmi’s influence in your career.</p>

<p><strong>Gemini (21 May-21 June)</strong></p>

<p>The ingredient of charm is sprinkled throughout everything they do. The Gregarious and refined. Fresh new ideas come easily to them. They are ruled over by mercury that creates an insatiable curiosity. They have a great capacity with words and the ability to communicate in most arena. Geminis are constantly being made and remade every day. Keeping something made of silver with you at all times can help you concentrate on your aim. Being reckless will adversely affect you in your growth so the silver will keep you grounded and help you focus.</p>

<p><strong>Cancer (22 June – 23 July)</strong></p>

<p>Diplomatic, sensitive and responsible. They care and can be tough in business at the same time. Being a water sign they are attuned to the world of intuition, aware of other’s needs. Masters of quiet persistent pressure that usually make others give in. For growth in career and removal of obstacles in promotion offer seven portions of cereal to birds. Cancerians can make a good career as bureaucrats or public relation professionals due to their ability to handle situation with diplomacy.</p>

<p><strong>Leo (24 July- 23 August)</strong></p>

<p>Leo’s are natural leaders and love attention. They aim high in life and make some of the best bosses. They like to be in the decision-making panel and strive hard to reach there. They would do well in politics where they can use their powers well and would make good teachers too. Many actors are born under this sign too. Wearing a sphatik /white crystal bead around your neck on a Friday will prove beneficial for your career.</p>

<p><strong>Virgo (24 August-23 September)</strong></p>

<p>Virgos are practical, cool-headed, meticulous and honest. They are totally reliable and are not very loud people. They have amazing memories and are health conscious. They make great managers, statisticians, and editors. Since they are good at researching, they can be great detectives too.</p>

<p>Worship Lord Kaal Bhairav –Lord Kaal Bhairav Nath is the furious form of Lord Shiva. He is also the Adhipathi Dev of Saturn, so his worship delivers employment.</p>

<p><strong>Libra (24 September-23 October)</strong></p>

<p>Librans are diplomatic, pleasant but sometimes moody. Their sign of balance can be represented well by placing people on one scale and understanding them on the other. They would know how to handle foreign relations. They are energetic and can be pleasantly argumentative. They would make good lawyers. They would do well in the hospitality industry and administrative department. Regularly offer water to a Peepal tree, the greatness of Peepal tree is even mentioned in our ancient scriptures. Its worship propitiate Lord Shiva himself and also one of the benevolent planet in Astrology (Jupiter)</p>

<p><strong>Scorpio (23 October-22 November)</strong></p>

<p>Scorpio is hard working, intelligent, resourceful and smart. They would do well as physicians and surgeons. They would be an asset in the armed forces as they know how to command. Because of their smart brain and intuition, they would excel in espionage or as a secret agent. Worship Lord Saturn is the key significator of servitude in astrology. Offering boiled rice to crows who helps in pacifying Saturn helps in improving your profession</p>

<p><strong>Sagittarius (23 November-22 December)</strong></p>

<p>Sagittarius are fun-loving outdoor people who have a knack of doing everything well. They are full of energy and are sporty too. They can use their enthusiasm to work in administrative jobs, lawyers or as teachers. They are great in Public Relations and know how to get their work done. A travel related job would be ideal too.Lord Ganesha is known as Vigna Vinashaka and worshipping lord Ganesha every morning can help you to surround yourselves with the positivity and help you focus on your aim rather than the hurdles in front of you</p>

<p><strong>Capricorn (23 December-20 January)</strong></p>

<p>Capricorns are motivated, determined, responsible, organized and hardworking people. They are great at accounting and maths and are notorious workaholics. They make good businessmen because of their shrewdness and lawyers with their logical thinking. They are a pro with technology too.Offering sweetened bread to birds or stray animals can help pacify the Rahu here.</p>

<p><strong>Aquarius(21 January-19 February)</strong></p>

<p>Aquarians are honest, patient, hardworking, kind and original thinkers. They are easy with money and in no way hoarders. They would do great as scientists and aviators with their intellect, precision, and ideas. They have their own creative ideas that they could showcase through poetry or music.Chanting Sri Krishna Chalisa or donating yellow items (like yellow lentils, clothes, fruits, and metals), these can help in you to focus more on your aim by keeping your heart at peace.</p>

<p><strong>Pisces(20 February-20 March)</strong></p>

<p>Pisces are artistic, sensitive, independent and generous people. They do best in fields that can show their creativity, like the theater, salons, painting etc. They won’t do so great in a 9-5 job where they will be bound to a routine. They make good Philanthropists. Conducting a Lakshmi Narayana Puja can help you improve your financial condition. Goddess Lakshmi is known to help her disciples at the time of dire economic pressures. Including Lakshmi puja in your daily routine can help you in the long run.</p>

